MOSCOW, May 7 (Sputnik) – No circumstances or obstacles should stand in Russia’s way as the country determine its future, Russian President Vladimir Putin said at his inauguration ceremony on Monday. “Of course, we must stay at the same pace as global changes, to build our agenda of a breakthrough development so that no obstacles or circumstances would prevent us, and only us, from determining our own future, to implement our ambitious plans and dreams,” Putin said. The president added that Russia had learned to defend its interests​​​. “We have learned to defend our interests, and revived pride for our motherland, our traditional values. Experience demonstrates that today we need to safeguard the achieved, and to move forward on this basis,” Putin stated.